This paper deals with deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of slates and attention mechanisms also suggests a focus on natural language processing and information retrieval, which are covered by the cs.IR and cs.CL sub-categories. The use of feature vectors and high-dimensional spaces suggests a focus on data science and machine learning, which are covered by the cs.DS and cs.LG sub-categories. Overall, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.DS, and cs.CL.
